'''Aldemir Bendine''' (born 10 December 1963) was the chief executive officer (CEO) of [[Petrobras]].

Bendine worked for [[Banco do Brasil]] since the age of 15, rising to CEO. He has been named CEO of Brazil’s state-run oil company Petrobras, leaving his position as head of Brazil’s Central Bank, the Petrobras directive board has confirmed. The new chief of Brazil's oil company was born in 1963, and has worked at the country's largest bank by assets, [[Banco do Brasil]] from the age of 15, eventually becoming its CEO.<ref name="Buenos Aires Herald">{{cite web|title=Executive Profile: Petrobras confirms Aldemir Bendine as CEO|url=http://www.buenosairesherald.com/article/181355/petrobras-confirms-aldemir-bendine-as-ceo|accessdate=2 June 2016}}</ref>

Bendine has been CEO of [[Petrobras]] from February 2015 to May 2016.<ref name=Bloomberg>{{cite web|title=Executive Profile: Aldemir Bendine|url=https://www.bloomberg.com/research/stocks/people/person.asp?personId=54763305&ticker=BBAS3:BZ|website=Bloomberg|accessdate=20 June 2015}}</ref>

Aldemir Bendine has been a [[BRF bank|BRF]] board member since September 2015.<ref name=Valor>{{cite web|title=Bendine gets board role at BRF |url=http://www.valor.com.br/international/news/4334790/bendine-gets-board-role-brf|accessdate=2 June 2016}}</ref>

He was arrested in Operation Car Wash (Portuguese: Operação Lava Jato), ongoing criminal investigation being carried out by the Federal Police of Brazil in July 27, 2017 
<ref name=G1 >{{cite web|title=PF prende Aldemir Bendine, ex-presidente da Petrobras, em nova fase da Lava Jato |url=https://g1.globo.com/pr/parana/noticia/pf-cumpre-mandados-da-42-fase-da-operacao-lava-jato.ghtml|accessdate=18 February 2018}}</ref>

He was charged by federal prosecutors with “passive corruption”, money laundering, criminal organization and obstruction of justice.<ref name=Valor|>{{cite web|title=Former-Petrobras-ceo-charged-corruption |url=http://www.valor.com.br/international/news/5090572/former-petrobras-ceo-charged-corruption |accessdate=18 February 2018}}</ref>

